          <body>
              <div type="edition" subtype="primary" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="la" resp="#IG" source="http://zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GQN8UZSI">
                      <div type="textpart" subtype="lamina"> <!-- remove corresp attribute from textparts -->
                             <ab>
                                 <lb n="1" style="text-direction:r-to-l"/>Adici
                          </ab>
                      </div>
                   <div type="textpart" subtype="handle">
                      <ab>
                          <lb n="1" style="text-direction:r-to-l"/>Hilari <supplied reason="subaudible">servi</supplied>
                       </ab>
                  </div>
              </div>
              <div type="apparatus">
                  <listApp>
                      <app><note>Text from CIL</note></app>
                  </listApp>
              </div>
              <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#IG">
                  <p>of Adicius. (seal for use by) Hilarus (slave).</p>
              </div>
              <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#IG">
                  <p>di Adicius. (timbro ad uso di) Hilarus (schiavo).</p>
              </div>
              <div type="commentary">
                  <p xml:lang="en">The name on the handle generally indicates the slave delegated to use the seal on behalf of the owner, whose name is on the lamina. 
                      The presence of the name on the handle may be indicative of the existence, originally, of multiple copies of the seal, used by different delegates.</p>
              </div>
